[debug] [2026-05-26T18:32:36.369Z] Command:       C:\Program Files\nodejs\node.exe C:\Users\homelab\AppData\Roaming\npm\node_modules\firebase-tools\lib\bin\firebase.js database:set --project persinfo-df93f --force -d {createdAt:1748304000000,description:Deployed a full SIEM stack with Wazuh, enrolled all three hosts as agents, ran brute force detection tests from a Kali Linux attack VM, and wired up the Cradlepoint IBR900 router to forward syslog into the SIEM.,imageUrl:,sections:[{summary:The homelab now has a working SIEM (Security Information and Event Management) stack. All three hosts are enrolled as Wazuh agents and generating real security events. Brute force detection was validated with a Kali Linux attack VM.,title:Overview},{content:[{items:[wazuh.manager - agent enrollment on ports 1514/1515,wazuh.indexer - OpenSearch on port 9200,wazuh.dashboard - Kibana-based UI at https://192.168.50.10:5601],type:list}],summary:Deployed the Wazuh single-node Docker stack at E:\\Containers\\wazuh\\single-node\\. The stack runs three containers: wazuh.manager (agent comms), wazuh.indexer (OpenSearch), and wazuh.dashboard (web UI at https://192.168.50.10:5601).,title:Wazuh SIEM Deployment},{content:[{items:[Agent 001 - se (192.168.50.10, Windows Server),Agent 002 - louserver (192.168.50.20, Ubuntu 26.04 VM) - custom ossec.conf monitoring /var/log/auth.log and /var/log/syslog,Agent 003 - ws (192.168.50.11, Windows workstation)],type:list}],summary:Three agents enrolled across the homelab network. The web-server VM (louserver) required a manually written ossec.conf due to a config incompatibility between the 4.14.5 installer and the 4.9.2 manager.,title:Agent Enrollment},{content:[{items:[Rule 5710 - sshd: attempt to login using a non-existent user,Rule 5712 - sshd: brute force attempt (MITRE T1110),Rule 5763 - sshd: maximum authentication attempts exceeded,Confirmed in Wazuh Discover - 1,384 events captured in a 30-minute window],type:list}],summary:Spun up a Kali Linux 2026.1 VM (Hyper-V on se, 192.168.50.40) and ran SSH brute force attacks against louserver. Wazuh detected the attack and fired the expected rule chain within seconds.,title:Red Team Validation - Kali Brute Force},{content:[{type:code,value:<ossec_config>\n  <remote>\n    <connection>syslog</connection>\n    <port>514</port>\n    <protocol>udp</protocol>\n    <allowed-ips>192.168.50.1</allowed-ips>\n  </remote>\n</ossec_config>}],summary:Configured the Cradlepoint IBR900 (192.168.50.1) to forward syslog to the Wazuh manager on 192.168.50.10:514 UDP. Added the syslog remote listener to the manager ossec.conf.,title:Router Syslog to SIEM},{content:[{type:code,value:# List all agents\ndocker exec -it single-node-wazuh.manager-1 /var/ossec/bin/agent_control -l\n\n# Restart manager after config changes\ndocker restart single-node-wazuh.manager-1\n\n# Verify syslog listener\ndocker exec single-node-wazuh.manager-1 ss -ulnp | grep 514}],summary:Quick reference for managing the Wazuh stack.,title:Useful Commands}],tags:[homelab,security,wazuh,siem,kali,linux,networking],title:Homelab Security Stack - Wazuh SIEM, Kali Red Team & Network Monitoring,updatedAt:1748304000000} /7cIh8rrhVNOjjj5CBDgb3IlqzEh2/journalArticles/1748304000000
